{"title_page": "Ayase Ueda", "text_new": "{{short description|Japanese footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Ayase Ueda <br> \u4e0a\u7530\u7dba\u4e16\n| fullname = Ayase Ueda\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1998|8|28}}\n| birth_place = [[Mito, Ibaraki|Mito]], [[Japan]]\n| height={{height|m=1.82}}\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[Kashima Antlers]]\n| clubnumber = 36\n| youthyears1 = 2017\u20132019 | youthclubs1 = [[Hosei University]]\n| years1 = 2019\u2013 | clubs1 = [[Kashima Antlers]] | caps1 = 13 | goals1 = 4\n| nationalyears1 = 2018  | nationalteam1 = [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan U-21]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 2\n| nationalyears2 = 2017\u2013 | nationalteam2 = [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan U-23]] | nationalcaps2 = 7 | nationalgoals2 = 3\n| nationalyears3 = 2019\u2013 | nationalteam3 = [[Japan national football team|Japan]]               | nationalcaps3 = 6 | nationalgoals3 = 0\n|medaltemplates=\n{{Medal|Country|{{Fb|JPN}}}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[Asian Games]]}}\n{{Medal|S|[[2018 Asian Games|2018 Jakarta-Palembang]]|[[Football at the 2018 Asian Games \u2013 Men|Team]]}}\n| pcupdate = 14:52, 9 December 2019 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = December 18, 2019\n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''Ayase Ueda'''|\u4e0a\u7530\u7dba\u4e16|Ueda Ayase|born August 28, 1998}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[Association football|football]] player.<ref>https://www.jleague.jp/player/1615529/#attack</ref>\n\n==International career==\nOn May 24, 2019, Ueda was called up by [[Japan national football team|Japan]]'s head coach [[Hajime Moriyasu]] to feature in the [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica|Copa Am\u00e9rica]] played in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jfa.jp/eng/news/00021323/|title=SAMURAI BLUE (Japan National Team) Squad, Schedule - CONMEBOL Copa America Brazil 2019 (6/14\u20137/7)|publisher=JFA|date=24 May 2019}}</ref> He's the only player of that roster coming from a university, despite being registered for [[Kashima Antlers]]. He made his debut on 17 June 2019 in the game against Chile, as a starter.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[CONMEBOL]]|url=http://estadisticas.conmebol.com/html/v3/index.html?channel=deportes.futbol.copaamerica.462516&lang=es_LA|title=Japan v Chile game report|date=17 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Club statistics==\n''Updated to 22 February 2019''.<ref>Nippon Sports Kikaku Publishing inc./\u65e5\u672c\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u4f01\u753b\u51fa\u7248\u793e, [https://www.amazon.co.jp/J1-J3%E9%81%B8%E6%89%8B%E5%90%8D%E9%91%91%E3%83%8F%E3%83%B3%E3%83%87%E3%82%A3%E7%89%88-2019-NSK-MOOK/dp/4905411629 \"J1&J2&J3\u9078\u624b\u540d\u9451\u30cf\u30f3\u30c7\u30a3\u7248 2019 (NSK MOOK)\"], 9 February 2019, Japan, {{ISBN|978-4905411628}} (p. 28 out of 289)</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Club performance\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Season\n! Club\n! League\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n! colspan=3 |Japan\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | [[Emperor's Cup|Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | [[J. League Cup|League Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n|[[2019 J1 League|2019]]||rowspan=\"1\"|[[Kashima Antlers]]||rowspan=\"1\"|[[J1 League]]||0||0||0||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n!colspan=3|Total\n!0||0||0||0||0||0||0||0\n|}\n\n==National team statistics==\n<ref>{{NFT player}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! colspan=\"3\" | [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[2019 Japan national football team|2019]]||6||0\n|-\n!Total||6||0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|74629}}\n*{{J.League player}}\n*{{Soccerway|ayase-ueda/551425}}\n\n{{Kashima Antlers squad}}\n{{Japan squad 2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ueda, Ayase}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Hosei University alumni]]\n[[Category:Association footba